framework

Class Implementation

  • java.lang.Object
    • framework.Implementation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentReferences
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BasicBatch, BasicExternalInformationPort, BasicInputOutputHandler, BasicKeyGenerator, BasicMessageProcessor, BasicPool, BasicSystemTimeClock, BasicUserDatabase

    public abstract class Implementation
extends Object
implements ComponentReferences
    The abstract class Implementation implements the ComponentReferences interface, so that a particular implementation of a component knows about all Controllers of all other components of the mix. Furthermore, it can access the other controllers' implementations, the logger, the mix itself and the settings of the mux.
    Author:
    Daniel Kaiser

      • setController

        public void setController(Controller controller)
        In this method, the controller of the particular implementation is set; furthermore, all components of the controller are linked with this implementation. Then the mix is registered with the implementation and the implementation is registered with the mix. Finally, the pseudo constructor of the implementation class is run.
        Parameters:
        controller - The controller of the implementation.

      • constructor

        public abstract void constructor()
        This pseudo Constructor is run after the instantiation of the implementation class by the ClassLoader.

      • initialize

        public abstract void initialize()
        This method is run after the references to and from all the other components are set. Here data could be send to other components, if needed.

        After returning from this method, the current implementation should be able to start to work.
